         for high-demand Navy capabilities, including underwater construction and diving programs such as Underwater Construction
         Team (UCT) Diver, Navy First Class Diver, Navy Master Diver, and UCT Master Construction Diver, as well as training
         focused on homemade explosives identification and advanced improvised explosive device (IED) disposal. These resources
         support curriculum development, specialized training delivery, and the sustainment of expeditionary construction and
         facilities management capabilities required to operate in contested and high-risk environments. Funding in these training
         programs ensures the Navy develops and maintains highly skilled personnel with the technical expertise necessary to execute
         expeditionary missions, mitigate explosive hazards, and sustain operational readiness in support of Fleet requirements. MIP
