      xiv)Naval Aviation Schools Command (NASC). Increase required to restore aviation training capacity following the level of               907
         risk the Navy accepted in FY 2026. This level of risk cannot be sustained in FY 2027 without creating delays in the aviation
         training pipeline and impacting the timely production of qualified aviators. Additional resources support expanded ground
         and flight training necessary to strengthen throughput and ensure aviators are prepared to meet fleet requirements. This
         investment is essential to maintaining aviation readiness and enabling the Navy to meet operational demands. (Baseline:
         $14,036)
      xv)Navy Foreign Language. Resources increased to support the Naval Education and Training Command (NETC) overseas                       548
         Foreign Language Testing and Language Testing Centers in Naples, Italy and Yokosuka, Japan as part of the Defense
         Language Institute right-sizing initiative. Funding sustains testing capabilities that assess and certify foreign language
         proficiency for personnel supporting operational, intelligence, and joint mission requirements. These resources ensure timely
         language qualification and readiness for forward-deployed forces supporting Fleet and combatant command operations. MIP
         impact $408. (Baseline: $2,176)
