      ii)Resources decreased due to reduced information technology contract support for six Defense Business Systems, including the          -37
         Corporate Enterprise Training Activity Resource System (CeTARS), Corporate Automated Resource Information System
         (CARIS), Navy Enlisted Advancement System (NEAS), Naval Education and Training Future Officer and Citizenship User
         System (NETFOCUS), My Education, and the Learning Assessment System (LAS). The decrease reflects the removal of
         Other Direct Costs (ODC) and travel-related Contract Line Item Numbers (CLINs), planned contract re-competes beginning
         in FY27, and a reduction in overall IT contract support services. These systems support enterprise training management,
         personnel advancement processes, and resource management functions across the Navy. While funding is reduced, continued
         support for these systems remains critical to sustaining acquisition, financial management, logistics, and training management
         capabilities that support Fleet readiness and mission execution. (Baseline: $178,702)
      iii)Navy Advancement In Rate: Resources decreased in Advancement Examination Readiness Reviews (AERRs) supplies and                    -90
         equipment requirement. AERRs support the exam development process during which Fleet Subject Matter Experts (FSMEs)
         convene to maintain psychometric standard minimums for the Navy's advancement exam banks in order to effectively
         discriminate rating knowledge for more than 230K advancement-eligible Sailors annually. (Baseline: $9,382)
      iv)Authoring Instructional Materials (AIM): Resources decreased due to the IT Contract Support re-compete. IT contract                -138
         support provides Central Design Activity (CDA) services commensurate with supporting technical tasks necessary to manage
         the wide range of IT programs that support the Naval Education and Training Command (NETC) mission. (Baseline: $1,089)
      v)Visual Information: Resources decreased due to the Supply Chain Management Contract re-compete, which provides                      -229
         audiovisual support throughout the Manpower, Personnel, Training and Education (MPT&E) domain. (Baseline: $688)
      vi)Command and Administration: Resources decreased due to an internal realignment to fund two civilian Full-Time Equivalent           -262
         (FTE) billets providing financial management and administrative support. These personnel support headquarters functions
         within Bureau of Naval Personnel (BUPERS) and Naval Education and Training Command (NETC) in Pensacola, Florida.
         The billets provided financial management, financial analysis, accounting, and administrative support services necessary to
         support resource management operations and program oversight across the command. (Baseline: $21,242; -2 civilian FTE)
      vii)Training Network Support: Resources decreased in IT Contract Support for TRANET Network (TN) due to the removal of                -295
         Other Direct Cost (ODC) and travel Contract Line Item Numbers (CLINs). (Baseline: $9,388)
      viii)Reduce funding to align with the adjusted Federal Employees Retirement System (FERS) contribution rates. These                   -327
         adjustments incorporate updated actuarial assumptions, workforce demographics shifts, and revised projections of retirement
         liabilities. (Baseline: $463,572)
      ix)CTC: Resources decreased in the Career-Long Learning Continuum (CLLC) phase of the program due to a change in system               -869
         maintenance costs for the electronic classroom training sites, which supports the Career Training Continuum efforts.
         (Baseline: $4,016)
      x)The reduction of funding for contracted services is undertaken in direct support of the President's executive order, which          -924
         prioritizes cost efficiency, transparency, and the consolidation of services. This measure represents a deliberate workforce
         optimization strategy designed to streamline resources while safeguarding against adverse impacts to modernization
         initiatives and overall mission effectiveness. (Baseline: $182,718)
