FY 2026 President's Budget Request                                                                                                                       303,177
1)Congressional Adjustments                                                                                                                                3,446
  a)Distributed Adjustments                                                                                                                                4,300
      i)FY26 Program Increase - US Naval Sea Cadet Corps (Baseline: $0)                                                                         4,300
  b)Undistributed Adjustments                                                                                                                               -854
      i)FY26 Projected Underexecution of Civilian Compensation (Baseline: $0)                                                                    -854
FY 2026 Current Estimate                                                                                                                                 306,623
Price Change                                                                                                                                               5,396
2)Program Increases                                                                                                                                       40,111
  a)One-Time FY 2027 Costs                                                                                                                                   869
      i)Resources increased for civilian personnel due to a one time FY26 reduction for projected under execution. The funding                   869
         Equips the production recruiter with training, vehicles, travel, OPE, and supplies. The accession program provides the
         applicant with food, lodging, and non-instrumental drug testing while processing through the Military Entrance Processing
         Station (MEPS) and associated travel. (Baseline: $57,627; +18 civilian FTE)
  b)Program Increase in FY 2027                                                                                                                           39,242
      i)Advertising: Resources increased to fund Manpower and Reserve Affairs (M&RA), Recruit Training Command (RTC)                           21,613
         nurturing, and Center of Influence (COI) campaigns used to increase awareness of the Department of Navy combat accession
         mission goals and replenish a depleted Delayed Entry Program. Funding will be utilized to create digital media online videos
         and ads; Navy television commercials on specific programming channels; and contribute to the management of social media
         sites and content placement. (Baseline: $147,501)
      ii)Recruiting: Resources increased for the recruiting functions. Funding restoral will allow for Intra Governmental Contract             16,269
         Services such as training, vehicles, travel, and supplies. (Baseline: $128,532)
      iii)Resources increased for the Department of the Navy's civilian performance award pool to 4 percent of the FY 2027 average               765
         annualized adjusted basic pay, providing the resources necessary to recognize high performance and incentivize excellence
         across the civilian workforce. This investment directly advances the Secretary of the War's priority to strengthen and
         empower the Department's civilian talent by ensuring performance awards remain competitive in a constrained labor market.
         (Baseline: $306,623)
      iv)Increase to invest in the human capital required to build the Navy of the future. The increase in civilian recruiting and IT            595
         specialists is essential to competing for and securing the nation's top talent in critical fields like cyber, AI, and engineering.
         This directly supports the SECNAV's strategic imperative to build a more capable and modernized force by ensuring we can
         recruit the highly skilled individuals needed to operate it. (Baseline: $57,627; +6 civilian FTE)
3)Program Decreases                                                                                                                                       -90,990
  a)One-Time FY 2027 Costs                                                                                                                                 -4,376
      i)Recruiting: Resources decreased due to the FY26 Congressional funding for the Naval Sea Cadet Corps (NSCC) training                    -4,376
         program during enactment. (Baseline: $128,532)
