C. Reconciliation of Increases and Decreases                                                                                                Amount        Total
  b)Program Decrease in FY 2027                                                                                                                         -86,614
      i)Reduce funding to align with the adjusted Federal Employees Retirement System (FERS) contribution rates. These                        -255
         adjustments incorporate updated actuarial assumptions, workforce demographics shifts, and revised projections of retirement
         liabilities. (Baseline: $306,623)
      ii)Information Technology: Resources decreased for Naval Identity Services. Reduction is attributed to Recruit Training                 -966
         Command's (RTC's) transition to voice over internet phone (VOIP) that resulted in lower contracted service cost, equipment,
         and planned workforce reshaping. (Labor -$59) (Non Labor -$917) (Baseline: $30,590)
      iii)Implements a strategic reduction of civilian Full-Time Equivalents (FTEs) and funding for Direct and Working Capital Fund          -1,164
         employees in compliance with Executive Order 14210. This workforce optimization is facilitated through voluntary
         separation tools, including the Deferred Resignation Program (DRP), to eliminate redundancies and restore accountability.
         (Baseline: $57,627; -11 civilian FTE)
      iv)Resources decreased funding for legacy systems, non-Jupiter data environments, system retirements, and other undefined             -18,095
         investments and networks documented in Department of the Navy Network Consolidation to Enterprise Information
         Technology Services guidance. (Baseline: $306,623)
      v)Reduces funding for printing and reproduction to align with historical execution levels and ensure alignment with the               -30,761
         priorities of the Secretary of War to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of our mission and business operations.
         (Baseline: $147,501)
      vi)The reduction of funding for contracted services is in direct support of the President's executive order, which prioritizes cost   -35,373
         efficiency, transparency, and the consolidation of services. This measure represents a deliberate workforce optimization
         strategy designed to streamline resources while safeguarding against adverse impacts to modernization initiatives and overall
         mission effectiveness. (Baseline: $306,623)
