INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_541$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 4A3M
                                                                                                                                                          (Page 11 of 11)
                                                                              Department of the Navy
                                                                     FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                         Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                            Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                                       Activity Group: Servicewide Support
                                                        Detail by Subactivity Group: Military Manpower and Personnel Mgt
I. Description of Operations Financed:

Funds requested in the Military Manpower and Personnel Management line item support the direct staff offices of the Secretary of the Navy and the Chief of Naval Operations, as
well as various functional activities reporting to them. It also resources the headquarters staffs of Navy operational and systems commands. Finally, this budget funds centrally-
managed programs on behalf of the Department of the Navy (DON).

The Bureau of Naval Personnel (BUPERS) supports the Deputy Chief of Naval Operations (Manpower, Personnel, Training and Education) (DCNO-MPTE) in providing Human
Resource support for the US Navy, to include officer and enlisted personnel manpower determinations, accessions, training, personnel assignments, career development, personnel
administration, and other functions. Operations include Enterprise Support; Force Development; and Force Management.

The programs financed include:

BRIGS: Brigs Charleston, Miramar, and their respective detachments (Chesapeake and Pearl Harbor) provide state-of-the-art correctional services to all branches of the military.
The Brigs also provide military escort services for adjudged prisoners and deserters. Funding supports facility infrastructure maintenance and repair, security system maintenance
contracts, and specialized locking and security sensitive equipment. Funding also supports inmate treatment programs for Alcohol and Drug abuse, violent and sexual offenders,
Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder, medical, and mental health counseling. To prepare prisoners for successfully returning to a productive civilian life, the Brigs provide useful skill-
set and transitional training for inmates.

Financial Audit Sustainment and Financial Improvement Plan: The Financial Audit Sustainment program works to improve the Navy's financial processes, controls, and
information to attain a favorable financial audit. The Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR) Plan outlines the strategy, priorities, and methodology for achieving
these objectives.

Information Technology (IT) Infrastructure and Resources: This category consists of the Chief Information Officer (CIO) Office, Deputy Chief of Naval Operations
(Manpower, Personnel, Training, and Education) (DCNO-MPTE), the Information Management/Information Technology (IM/IT) Division which designs, selects, and provides
affordable next generation technologies for the total force; the Chief Information Officer (CIO) Support Office, Navy Personnel Command (NPC), which provides NPC
Headquarters level support and oversight for IT operations supporting MyNavy Human Resource (HR) systems in Millington, TN; Information Technology (IT) Resources
Management, which provides funding for all Civilian IT labor for NPC who support all BUPERS IT software programs used internally for business processes and externally by
Sailors accessing MyNavy HR applications; Service Unique Desk Applications, the hardware and software maintenance contracts for the core system which hosts the personnel
management system and provides Millington IT helpdesk support Navy Personnel Command (NPC) Communications, funding voice telephone lines, fax/modem lines, video
teleconferencing capabilities (VTC), audio conferencing calls, headsets, cellular phones, data cards, system administration and customer support, repair and installation
management, and toll-free services for personnel; Data Center Cloud Migration, which funds migration and maintenance of Navy systems to a secure enterprise cloud environment
in conjunction with modernization per the CIO mandate to migrate to the cloud; Fleet Engagement, provides BUPERS website oversight, compliance, training and content
management of more than 6,000 web pages; Business Transformation, funds modernization of internal business IT processes; and IT Messaging System, the system which allows
commands to share Permanent Change of Station (PCS) orders and assignment notes.

Legacy System Sustainment: MyNavy Human Resources (HR) currently requires many IT systems, related infrastructure, and IT support to provide personnel and records
management for the Navy. The IT systems include the Navy Standard Integrated Personnel System (NSIPS), used to track HR related items for all members of the Navy from the
initial accession contract to the departure from Navy service; Electronic Military Personnel Record System (EMPRS), which is the official personnel records management system
and the repository for Official Military Personnel File images of active-duty, reserve, and separated personnel and provides decision support for the Selection Board process,
         583                                                                                                                                                  $$, $$12b8162951fced295896e7b53f48e8afa2e6dcbbef56462b95169c43169d0407$$, $$O&M/FY27/Navy/OMN_Book.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_542$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 4A4M
                                                                                                                                                                    (Page 1 of 15)
                                                                                 Department of the Navy
                                                                         FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                           Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                              Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                                          Activity Group: Servicewide Support
                                                          Detail by Subactivity Group: Military Manpower and Personnel Mgt
Mobilization, Casualty Assistance, Distribution, and Entitlements; BUPERS Online, an IT application which hosts 26 different applications which provides Sailors and Commands
with self-service access to official personnel records, performance appraisals, fitness reports, and official orders; Billet Based Distribution, a module added to the Career
Management System to automatically align enlisted sailors to billets; PERSTEMPO, the program which tracks deployment days of individual service members and payments due
for deployment days exceeding mandated thresholds; Career Waypoints (CWAY), a critical Navy staffing tool used to screen, match, and assign Sailors to positions throughout the
Navy during initial enlistment, reenlistments, and throughout their military careers; Navy/Marine Corps Mobilization Processing System (NMCMPS), which provides end-to-end
command visibility and control of integrated augmentation processes and automated work-flows, ranging from requesting, approving, sourcing, and writing orders for
requirements, to tracking, accounting, collecting data, and coordinating during activation/deactivation; Navy Retention and Monitoring System (NRMS), a web-enabled business
intelligence tool for staff and Fleet users to compute a wide array of tasks related to Active/Reserve standardized reenlistment, attrition, Perform to Serve statistics, and reserve
affiliation statistics; Brigs' Corrections Management Information Technology System (CORMIS), the Department of Navy's electronic records management system and Naval
offender management program; Navy Department Awards Web Service (NDAWS), the Navy's official database that stores DoW and foreign awards for Active Duty and Reserve
Personnel; Military Personnel Navy (MPN) Appropriation Justification Book Input and Compilation (MAJIC), which is used to assemble and construct the MILPERS, Navy
budget; N10 Financial Data Market, which provides a centralized combination of pay, billet, strength and Human Resource data; Distribution Incentive Management System,
which provides personnel managers with a decision support tool to allocate Navy personnel assignment (distribution) incentives to attract Sailors to jobs; and Defense Casualty
Information System, used to report Navy casualties, coordinate functions related to disposition of remains and personal effects, and provide notification and assistance to family
members.

Manpower Planning and Modeling: The manpower planning and modeling category consists of the Navy Manpower Analysis Center (NAVMAC) and the models program. The
models program funds contract support and contractor analysts for maintenance and updates to various manning models and analytical tools used by the Navy to project manning
requirements. NAVMAC develops and documents manpower requirements for all Fleet activities within the Navy; provides direct support to Chief of Naval Operations (CNO
(N1)) in managing the Navy manpower requirements programs; provides manpower requirements determination support for the Navy's acquisition programs and initiatives;
administers the officer and enlisted occupational classification structure; provides manpower technical consulting services in all areas to managers, claimants, and OPNAV
sponsors; provides functional management support for assigned manpower Automated Information Systems (AIS); provides direct support to CNO central authority to enforce
policy or provide additional technical guidance needed to achieve objectives of total force manpower management; and performs other manpower analyses as directed by higher
authority.

MyNavy Career Center (MNCC): MNCC provides operational and civilian personnel support for all program activities that support military pay and personnel, passenger
transportation, and identification card services for eligible personnel. This includes headquarters program management activities, the operation of the Navy Pay and Personnel
Support Center (NPPSC), Personnel Support Detachments (PSDs), and Customer Service Detachments (CSDs).

MyNavy Human Resource (HR) Information Technology (IT) Modernization and Sustainment: The Chief of Naval Personnel/N1/MyNavy HR enterprise is modernizing its
customer experience, operational processes, and business modes by taking maximum advantage of commercial technology to posture the Navy for the future. This modernization
integrates digital technology into all areas of the organization, fundamentally changing how it operates and delivers capability to each of the 412 Operational Activities (OA) and
provides value to Sailors. In order to remain effective, the HR business systems and activities must become more efficient; the infrastructure, business processes, and command
structure are being modernized to leverage commercial best practices and technologies that provide the Human Resources support the Navy needs. As part of this modernization,
the MyNavyHR organization will transition current IT and business architecture to a modern, cloud-based, customer-focused system by implementing a web-based mobile
MyNavy Portal (MNP) to streamline personnel action collection, processing, and records retention for Sailors, commands, and official personnel records. Modernization includes
an Enterprise Customer Relationship Management (eCRM) solution that will integrate business processes, supporting systems, and authoritative data in support of Navy Personnel
Command's (NPC's) My Navy Career Center (MNCC), Navy Recruiting Command (NRC), Navy Education & Training Command (NETC), and other commands that manage the
Navy workforce. It will deliver robust recruiting and accession functions with new capabilities and process improvements, provide a tiered human resource (HR) service delivery
       584                                                                                                                                                     $$, $$e4a4f82a20805c1d13391f79271a5f085bfb4e81b8dfb82bcc50832920c8cc14$$, $$O&M/FY27/Navy/OMN_Book.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:15.70986+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.om_activity_years (activity_code, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, ba, sag_short_code, title, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$OM_NAVY_X_543$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$OM_NAVY$$, NULL, NULL, $$Department of the Navy$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$, 4A4M
                                                                                                                                                                      (Page 2 of 15)
                                                                              Department of the Navy
                                                                      FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                         Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                            Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                                       Activity Group: Servicewide Support
                                                        Detail by Subactivity Group: Military Manpower and Personnel Mgt
model and develop workflow capabilities, provide a single source of account and contact data and deliver an enhanced single integrated prospecting system to recruit across all
mission areas anytime, anywhere. The Authoritative Data Environment (ADE) is an enterprise information management system that will migrate the existing legacy data
warehouses into a central data repository that is composed of a data warehouse, data lake, data management tools and an Application Program Interface (API) Layer. ADE will
provide an authoritative data-sharing framework, leveraging scalable and interoperable technologies as well as business intelligence and data analytic capabilities.

Personnel and Manpower Support Programs: The Personnel and Manpower Support Program consists of programs and offices which provide support to Navy personnel. Some
items funded include administrative labor for Washington Support Services (CNP), NPC, and corrections management; next-of-kin funeral program; forgotten widows; transitional
compensation for abused family members; dependent bedside travel program; medals and awards; temporary disability retired list program; mortuary affairs; uniform matters; the
International Cooperative Administrative Support Services (ICASS) program; selection and promotion boards; drug abuse prevention; retired affairs; physical readiness program;
total force contracts; career development, selection and classification program; and the prisoner-of-war and missing-in-action program.

Sexual Assault Prevention and Response (SAPR): The Office of Force Resiliency implements and manages the Navy-wide SAPR prevention and response efforts through
integrated programs, policies, leadership development, and oversight activities. The office has shifted from focusing on survivor support to prioritizing the prevention of
destructive behaviors committed by or against Navy service members, their families, and civilians Navy-wide.

NIWC Atlantic New Orleans Base Operations Support (BOS): The Navy Information Warfare Center Atlantic, New Orleans (NIWC LANT NOLA) mission is to improve
DoW readiness and operational capability by delivering effective enterprise-wide integrated information management/information technology solutions and life cycle support that
reduces cost of the supported functions.

Joint Air Logistic Information System (JALIS): Air logistics depend on JALIS. JALIS is a multipurpose on-demand automated scheduling program for operational scheduling,
aircraft management, and data analysis that allows DoW service personnel to submit airlift requirements for DoW personnel and cargo, air logistics flying units to communicate
their aircraft availability in a real-time graphic display, and designated scheduling organizations to compare airlift requirements to available aircraft and create mission
assignments. JALIS alerts users on mission information and changes via system displays and email. The geographically distributed JALIS scheduling capability moves thousands
of DoW personnel and tons of cargo annually in support of Navy Unique Fleet Essential Airlift, Army's Operational Support Airlift Agency (OSAA), US Transportation Command
(USTRANSCOM), and USMC.

Sea Warrior Manpower, Personnel, Training and Education (MPT&E) Business IT Systems: The Sea Warrior System Program Management Office (PMO), which falls
under Manpower, Logistics, and Business Solutions (MLB), is responsible for the integration of approximately 70 MyNavy HR applications. Sea Warrior is the Human Resources
(HR) component of CNO's Sea Power 21 Transformation Roadmap specifically focused on maximizing human capital and improving Fleet readiness by ensuring the right skills
are in the right place at the right time. Sea Warrior supports the sailor growth and developmental needs and enables the Navy to move toward a competency-focused, skill-oriented
position management for Navy personnel. The Sea Warrior Program Office provides acquisition and program management for MyNavy HR (formerly Navy Manpower, Personnel,
Training and Education (MPT&E)) information technology (IT) program.




