         Service programs provided to Sailors and their families. (Baseline: $123,354; +29 civilian FTE)
      viii)Increase funding for the Department of the Navy's civilian performance-award pool to 4 percent of the FY 2027 average           2,546
         annualized adjusted basic pay, providing the resources necessary to recognize high performance and incentivize excellence
         across the civilian workforce. This investment directly advances the Secretary of War's priority to strengthen and empower
         the Department's civilian talent by ensuring performance awards remain competitive in a constrained labor market. (Baseline:
         $195,363)
      ix)Manpower Planning and Modeling: Increase in civilian personnel funding to meet SECWAR's top priorities. Funding                   1,943
         provides program analysts for Navy Manpower Analysis Center (NAVMAC) to complete shoreline manpower requirements.
         These positions are critical for performing timely and accurate studies to determine the correct shoreline requirements to
         support the current and future Navy fleet. (Baseline: $26,526; +13 civilian FTE)
