         Funding supports SAPR programs across the Navy. These positions will manage the SAPR program throughout the Navy,
         develop and present educational materials and programs to US Navy civilian and military personnel, and ensure
         implementation of the Independent Review Council's recommendations for reducing SAPR in the military. The positions
         will also monitor and assess the impact of the program on sexual assaults within the Department of Navy. (Baseline: $7,785;
         +7 civilian FTE)
      xii)BRIGS: Increase in civilian personnel funding to support SECWAR's top priorities by sustaining essential prison                   867
