                                                                                                                                                             (Page 1 of 7)
                                                                            Department of the Navy
                                                                   FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                       Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                           Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                                     Activity Group: Servicewide Support
                                                               Detail by Subactivity Group: Medical Activities

Sexual Assault Prevention & Response (SAPR) – The DON's SAPR program continues to focus on increasing reporting and decreasing prevalence of sexual assault and sexual
harassment through primary prevention, refined response capabilities, treating victims with compassion, providing quality care, education, and addressing the barriers associated
with reporting sexual assault and sexual harassment.

Education and Training – Funding for this program supports resources required for the specialized skills, training, and professional development education programs for health
care personnel at Navy Medical Forces Support Command (NMFSC), Navy Medicine Operational Training Center (NMOTC), and the Navy Medicine Professional Development
Center (NMPDC). This also includes educational programs for health care personnel at federal, private sector academic institutions, and medical facilities. Supports the Navy
Medicine Surgeon General's Readiness Mission initiatives: Navy Corpsman (HM) Trauma Training (HMTT), HM Corpsman Training, and Role 2 Light Maneuver (R2LM).

*Starting in FY26, BA 4, Medical Activities (4A8M) are realigned to BA 1, Medical Readiness (1C1M) to consolidate Navy Medical Readiness resources into a single Budget
Activity/Sub-Activity Group to ensure consistency with other Services.


II. Force Structure Summary:

The Navy and Marine Corps Force Health Protection Command (formerly Navy and Marine Corps Public Health Center) establishes command and control of the two Navy Drug
Testing Laboratories, conducts tri-annual quality assurance inspections, and administrates the Tri-service reagent, consumable, maintenance contracts and equipment purchase with
the assistance of the Naval Medical Readiness Logistics Command and Washington Headquarters Services. The Chief of Naval Personnel establishes Navy urinalysis testing
requirements, ensures annual quality assurance inspections at the Navy drug labs, and manages the military education and training programs.
Navy Medicine's Medical Readiness programs evaluate and advise on Navy and Marine Corps matters and are the primary liaison in providing operational medical support to the
fleet surgeons and to the force medical officers of the Navy and Marine Corps.




