                                                                     FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                        Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                           Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                           Activity Group: Logistics Operations And Technical Support
                                                    Detail by Subactivity Group: Planning, Engineering, and Program Support
Other Programs:
NAVSEA Shipbuilding Support Office and Naval Vessel Register (NVR) provides technical and administrative functions in support of the NAVSEA industrial base. Provides for
the development and maintenance of the NVR.

Magnetic Silencing In-Service Support maintains and optimizes the onboard degaussing systems for all Navy, Coast Guard, and Military Sealift Command (MSC) ships.

Product Data Reporting and Evaluation Program (PDREP)/Supplier Product Quality (SPQ) Program supports new construction and Fleet readiness by ensuring critical material for
ships, submarines, and deep submergence systems is procured, repaired, and maintained by NAVSEA-approved sources.
The Supplier Product Quality (SPQ) program supports new construction and fleet readiness by ensuring critical material for ships, submarines and deep submergence systems is
procured, repaired and maintained by NAVSEA-approved sources Ships Critical Safety Item (CSI) legislation. The SPQ program also establishes Command policy for deterrence,
detection, mitigation and investigation programs for material fraud and counterfeit material. The programs managed include the following:
Director, Field Support Activities (FSA)

INDOPACOM
Provides funding for acquisition, planning, engineering, design, environmental protection, and physical security programs at USINDOPACOM. The Advanced Planning funding
(previously known as "Site Assessments") is required to close critical information gaps for posture footprint (MILCON) requirements directly supporting the USINDOPACOM
Independent Assessment of the Pacific Deterrence Initiate (PDI) posture and basing infrastructure plan. Across a three-year plan INDOPACOM intends to fully assess the theater
to produce a comprehensive Theater Infrastructure Master Plan; and fully assess the footprint gap and produce a plan to close the gap. The funds will cover posture footprint
assessments, project identification and the development of projects for MILCON in FY26 and beyond. Advanced Planning funds are used by INDOPACOM to support critical site
assessments and requirements development of Aerial Port of Debarkation (APOD) and Seaport of Debarkation (SPOD) at TO BE Posture locations to 1) determine existing
capabilities, shortfalls, and new requirements; 2) to inform future year requirements; and 3) to successfully execute dynamic basing concepts as part of the PDI.

Naval Air Systems Command (NAVAIR)

NAVAIR maintains and prepares the upkeep of force protection and self-defense of its operational capabilities against Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS) threats. Requirement
drivers are based on Congressional direction, SECWAR and Service policy and guidance, as well as technical sustainment requirements of the Physical Security Programs.
Funding is provided to protect high value/critical Navy assets, and support public safety against threats from inadvertent or unlawful misuse of UAS. This funding is used for
procurement, fielding, sustainment, and training of Counter-Unmanned Aerial systems (C-UAS) for Navy C-UAS and C-UxS programs under the Physical Security Program
umbrella.

MANDATORY FUNDING JUSTIFICATION:

The FY 26 spend plan amount for Planning, Engineering, and Program Support includes $533,675 thousand of discretionary and $208,430 thousand of mandatory
(reconciliation) for a total of $742,105 thousand.


II. Force Structure Summary: N/A


