I. Description of Operations Financed:

        Naval Supply Systems Command (NAVSUP): Provides logistical and quality of life support to sailors around the world. The Enterprise executes the mission along
        several business lines: Quality of Life, Logistics Operations, Global Logistics, Supply Program, Business Systems and Material Handling Equipment. Across these
        business lines are distinct products and services that enable NAVSUP to support Navy requirements. These products and services play a key role in maintaining
        warfighter readiness and improving the quality of life for Sailors and their families.

        Sailor and Family Care

        NEXCOM: Provides sailors and their families quality goods and services at retail locations. Additional services include, Ship Stores that support sailors while afloat,
        NEXMARTs (small grocery stores in remote locations), and Navy Lodges.

        Clothing Uniform Management: Provides life-cycle management and in-service engineering activity functions for Navy uniforms and for general-purpose organizational
        clothing.

        Household Goods Services: Supports operations and services relating to moving Sailors, their families and household goods worldwide.

        Postal Services: Provides operations and services of post office functions aboard all USS and USNS ships, and ashore facilities worldwide.

        Navy Cash: Gives sailors access to their money while deployed. Responsible for the disbursing policy, guidance, field examination group, Navy Cash® Automated Teller
        Machines (ATMs-at-sea) and the fleet assistance team.

        Food Service: The Navy Food Service Program provides operational and financial policy guidance designed to improve the quality of life for Sailors by ensuring our
        Navy general messes, ashore and afloat, efficiently and economically deliver high-quality nutritious foods that exceed customer expectations.



        Global Logistics Support

        NAVSUP Fleet Logistics Centers (FLCs) are strategically located throughout the United States and overseas which provide direct support to the warfighter.

        1.       NAVSUP FLC Bahrain
        2.       NAVSUP FLC Jacksonville
        3.       NAVSUP FLC Norfolk
        4.       NAVUSP FLC Pearl Harbor
        5.       NAVSUP FLC Puget Sound
        6.       NAVSUP FLC San Diego
        7.       NAVSUP FLC Sigonella
        8.       NAVSUP FLC Yokosuka
