                                                                                                                                                                    (Page 1 of 13)
                                                                               Department of the Navy
                                                                       FY 2027 President's Budget Submission
                                                                         Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                            Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                               Activity Group: Investigations And Security Programs
                                                           Detail by Subactivity Group: Investigative and Security Services

         Intelligence and Security (I&S) – serves as the principal civilian advisor on intelligence, defense sensitive support, signature reduction, sensitive activities, intelligence-
         related support activities, special operations and Irregular Warfare.

The Office of Naval Policy (ONP) – serves as the principal civilian advisor on defense strategy and policy, naval strategy, international affairs, security cooperation, naval force
posture (including related international agreements and arrangements), policy implications of emerging naval capabilities and concepts, military readiness and naval force design.

The Director of Office of Administration (DIRAD) includes the following programs:

Insider Threat program provides the oversight and capabilities to deter, detect and mitigate insider threats posed by individuals within the DON threats from Foreign Intelligence
Entities (FIE), and terrorists to include providing critical force, infrastructure and technology protection support.

Declassification of Records/DON Records Management Program holds responsibility to perform mandatory declassification reviews in compliance with the national policy for
classification and declassification of information by executive branch agencies. Records Management Program responsible for the lifecycle management of all DON records
including creation, maintenance, use, and disposition. Responsible for the transition to and management of DON's electronic records management environment, Record
Management 365 (RM365). Develops DON records management policy and guidance. Conducts DON-wide records management training and Command records management
inspections

SECNAV Directives, Forms, & Information Collections Management Program – is responsible for managing the procedures for developing and maintaining SECNAV policy,
including directives, instructions, manuals and notices via DON's authoritative correspondence and task management system (Enterprise Task Management Software Solution
ETMS 2). Ensures the non-duplication, common format, lawfulness, and authority of all DON forms. Ensures that information gathering does not adversely affect force strength,
and validates adherence to federal, DOW, and DON policies.

Operations Personnel and Support provides Intelligence products and services in direct support to US Navy Fleet and other operational Maritime Intelligence customers.
Funding supports Naval Special Warfare, Carrier/Expeditionary Strike Group deployments (CSG/ESG), Foreign Material Acquisition/Exploitation, Maritime Domain Awareness
and Support to MHQ/Maritime Operations Center (MOC).

  MANDATORY FUNDING JUSTIFICATION:

  The FY 26 spend plan amount for Investigative and Security Services includes $990,293 thousand of discretionary and $20,366 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation)
  for a total of $1,010,659 thousand.




