IV. Performance Criteria and Evaluation Summary:
 IV. Performance Criteria and Evaluation Summary:

 Metric Description: Measures the ability to provide Ready For Issue (RFI) equipment and supplies to combatant commanders.
 Metric #1: Attainment Rate = Equipment on-hand / Prepositioning Objective
 Metric #2: Readiness Rate = Equipment on-hand in RFI condition / Equipment on-hand

 Performance Goal: 90% Attainment Rate and 95% Readiness Rate.
 Data Source: U.S. Marine Corps Installations and Logistics; Logistics Plans, Policies, Strategic Mobility Division.

 (# of Units)                                                   FY 2024         FY 2025       FY 2026
 Prepositioning Objective*                                        8,295           8,232         8,232
 Equipment on-hand**                                              7,797           7,875         8,067
 Equipment on-hand in RFI condition                               7,407           7,540         7,985
 Attainment Rate                                                   94%             97%           98%
 Readiness Rate                                                    95%             96%           97%

 FY 2025 and FY 2026 Inventory requirements represent current program objectives and does not include equipment needed to establish future ashore prepositioning sites in
 INDOPACOM. Decisions are pending for the services' equipping strategy and the future ashore site locations and capabilities.

 Current inventory:
 - FY 2025 on-hand quantities represent current equipment status reporting dated May 21, 2025.
 - Attainment and Readiness rates reduced from previous year due to changes in strategic assessments and program objectives.
 - FY 2025 and FY 2026 on-hand quantities are projections based on the assumption that attainment will increase ~1% a year. Shortfalls will exist based on new equipment
 fielding priorities.
 - Equipment on-hand in ready for issue condition assumes that funding will remain at an adequate level to maintain a steady readiness rate.

 * FY 2025 Includes Marine Corps major ground readiness reportable equipment and principal end items in accordance with the NAVMC 2907 With Change 4, and FY 2026
 numbers are based on updated NAVMC 2907, which establishes the future approved inventory for the Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs (MCPP). It does not include
 consumable items, reparable items, munitions/ordnance, individual weapons, and aviation support equipment. FY 2025 and FY 2026 is based on current planning efforts and
 is subject to change.

 ** Equipment on-hand excludes excess items to the prepositioning objective.




